Description: monkey's audio lossless audio codec - binary
 Monkey's Audio is a highly efficient and popular lossless audio codec.
 .
 It is a tuned compressor for audio, like mp3, ogg, etc - but "lossless" in
 that it does not completely discard information, and performs more of a
 "zipping" that can be reversed at any time and generate the original source
 audio file (hence "lossless" vs "lossy").
 .
 Features:
  * Efficient (fast and great compression)
  * Perfect sound - absolutely no quality loss
  * Incorporates redundant CRC's to ensure proper decompression of data
  * Tagging support - extremely flexible APE Tags
 .
 Support for file format before 3.99 has been removed. If you have old files
 use the mac-old binary from the monkeys-audio-old package (support for all
 files before 3.99) or ffmpeg 2.0 (support from 3.93 to 4.11).

